<subSubSection id="65A7652EC0764B14FF014F6AFC83366B" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0764B14FF014F6AFC83366B" blockId="23.[192,1440,575,636]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FF014F6AFE8B364E" bold="true" box="[192,316,575,601]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The basal 4/5 of the elytron disc is testaceous and the apical 1/5 is black. These characteristics will distinguish the members of this species from congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65A7652EC0764B14FF014FDEFC173019" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0764B14FF014FDEFB863763" blockId="23.[191,1440,651,885]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FF014FDEFEDC36B2" bold="true" box="[192,363,651,677]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FEB44FD9FE1736B1" box="[373,416,652,678]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Size</emphasis>
. Length 
<quantity id="EA459B40C0764B14FDCD4FDEFDDF36B1" box="[524,616,651,678]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity id="EA459B40C0764B14FD024FD9FC9736B1" box="[707,800,652,678]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FCEF4FD9FCDE36B2" box="[814,873,652,677]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation id="B5862A20C0764B14FC054FD9FBA036B1" box="[964,1047,652,678]" captionStart="Figures 90–93" captionStartId="63.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1304,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-10@63.[192,1304,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="Figures 90–93. Habitus of Axina species. 90) Axina latilinea. 91) A. phallospina. 92) A. apicalis. 93) A. centrimaculata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565017/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Fig. 92</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FBE54FD9FBD636B1" box="[1060,1121,652,678]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium dark castaneous; antenna testaceous; prothorax bicolorous, venter, lower sides of pronotum, pterothorax, and legs black; pronotum disc castaneous; elytra bicolorous, mostly testaceous, epipleural margin and region in front of apex brown. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FF004FA6FF4C371A" box="[193,251,755,781]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons wider than length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 50/15. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FB134FA6FAA8371A" box="[1234,1311,755,781]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, concave at middle; PW/PL 115/125; elytra, asetiferous punctures scattered, punctures extend a short distance beyond elytron middle; EL/EW 420/80. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FC354E6DFBE93745" box="[1012,1118,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Aedeagus, phallobasic lobes very short, contiguous; phallic plates serrate; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0764B14FF014ED1FED337D6" blockId="23.[192,1440,900,961]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FF014ED1FE813789" bold="true" box="[192,310,900,926]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Variation.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FEFD4ED0FED03788" box="[316,359,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Size</emphasis>
. Length 9.5–13.0 mm; width 2.2–3.0 mm. Except for body size, the available specimens are quite homogeneous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0764B14FF014E87FC173019" blockId="23.[192,1441,977,1038]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FF014E87FECD37FC" bold="true" box="[192,378,977,1004]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected from 
<collectingCountry id="55AA7635C0764B14FD2A4E84FC8E37FC" box="[747,825,977,1003]" name="Bolivia" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
during October and November, some at 
<specimenCount id="3BBBFD2CC0764B14FACF4E87FAEB37FB" box="[1294,1372,978,1004]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="generic">
<quantity id="EA459B40C0764B14FACF4E87FAEE37FB" box="[1294,1369,978,1004]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.04" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" unit="m" value="404.0">404 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
From 
<collectingCountry id="55AA7635C0764B14FF034EA1FEB43019" box="[194,259,1012,1038]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Brazil</collectingCountry>
specimens were captured during November and December.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
